What you are seeing is the Musa Baoli. Baoli means the well, Water was supplied to the reservoir through underground pipes from a secret lake, Durgan Chiru. The source of the water was kept secret to prevent any poisoning of it. The step well used to be a work of art, with carvings and mound in and around. See if you can find anything now. The water was raised by the persian wheel was stored in overhead tanks at diffferent levels, which you will notice as you climb up. This collected water was distributed to various palaces, apartments, roof gardens, fountains and the citadel of the entire fort. All this was done through stone aquaducts and a network of earthen pipes through gravity. So advanced was the engineering poweress, technological capability and the mastery over design and function. 
